## 7. Technical Constraints

Auth needed: Yes — candidate profiles are private by default,
company access is gated.

Data storage: Structured conversation history per candidate.
Axis scores stored as ranges (min / baseline / max) not single
values — even if only baseline is shown in V1. Schema must
support range from day one.

APIs / integrations:
- LLM API for conversational agent (Claude Sonnet for
  conversations, Opus for complex contradiction detection)
- Supabase for candidate profile storage (schema-compatible
  with broader Tenure database)
- No third-party personality test APIs — by design

Deployment target: Web

Known complexity risks:
- Conversation continuity across sessions is technically
  non-trivial — agent needs to recall and reference prior
  answers accurately without hallucinating context
- Axis scoring from unstructured conversation requires
  reliable extraction logic — this is where the MVP is
  most likely to produce inaccurate profiles
- Company-side trust in a fit signal they can't interrogate
  is a product risk, not just a technical one

