## 8. Sprint 1 Definition

This is the only thing that ships first. Everything else is later.

What Sprint 1 includes:

- Conversational agent with the 4 founding questions,
  delivered as natural conversation not a form
- 5-axis spider diagram generated from conversation output
- Candidate-facing diagram view with validation prompt
- Simple correction mechanism — candidate flags an axis,
  writes a correction, agent acknowledges and updates
- Session memory — agent opens subsequent conversations
  with a reference to what was discussed before
- Manual matching backend — Boris reviews profiles and
  matches manually, no algorithm

What Sprint 1 explicitly excludes:

- Company-facing interface of any kind
- Automated match scoring
- Aspiration / dotted-line layer
- Range view (axis shows single baseline point only)
- Job-trigger conversations
- Any integration with external job boards or ATS

Sprint 1 is done when: 5 real candidates complete the full
conversation, see their diagram, validate it as accurate,
and at least 4 of 5 say the profile reflects something
true that their CV doesn't capture.

---

## 9. Success Metrics

Quantitative:

- Conversation completion rate: target >60% of candidates
  who start the first session complete all 4 questions
- Diagram accuracy rate: target >70% of candidates say
  "yes, this feels accurate" on first view
- Return rate: target >50% of candidates return for a
  second session within 7 days

Qualitative:

- Candidates describe the conversation as feeling different
  from a personality test — specifically: less evaluative,
  more like being understood
- At least one candidate says something like "this surfaced
  something I hadn't articulated before"
- Companies in manual pilot find the profile adds signal
  beyond the CV when making interview decisions

