## 10. Tool Recommendation

Recommended: Stitch → Lovable
Why: The candidate-facing conversation and diagram are
design-critical — the tone and feel of the interface
determines whether candidates trust the process. Stitch
for UX exploration and flow validation before committing
to build. Lovable for the React frontend with Supabase
backend, which stays schema-compatible with the broader
Tenure database.
Workflow: Stitch (conversation flow + diagram design) →
Lovable (build) → Supabase (profile storage)
Watch out for: The conversational agent logic is too
complex for Lovable alone — the LLM integration and
session memory will need Claude Code for the backend
conversation handling.

Alternative if conversation logic becomes the primary
complexity: Replit for full-stack control over the agent
logic, with Lovable handling only the frontend UI layer.

