## Open Questions

1. How does the agent handle a candidate who gives only
   short, guarded answers? Is there a minimum data threshold
   before a diagram is generated, or does a thin profile
   surface as explicitly incomplete?

2. What happens when a candidate's profile shifts significantly
   over time — does the old data get archived, weighted down,
   or replaced? The range model helps but needs a defined policy.

3. Company trust in the fit signal without seeing raw data —
   this needs a manual pilot with 2–3 companies before Sprint 2
   builds anything on the company side. Do not build company
   features until this is validated.

4. Tenure is not named publicly yet. The candidate-facing
   product in Sprint 1 should be testable without a public
   brand — consider whether this runs as an invite-only
   prototype under a neutral name during validation.
